Title: Unfinished Statue of a Man
Description: The top of a wrap-around garment is seen on this unfinished work.  It may have been intended as a royal statue, then altered for a private owner, which would explain the chiseled area on the forehead where the uraeus serpent, a symbol of royalty, may have been.
Provenance: Dikran Kelekian, New York and Paris; Henry Walters, Baltimore, 1911, by purchase; Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.
Creator: Egyptian
